CONJUGATION_TABLES.NOTE: In the 'Caite' we put a D' before a verb beginning with a vowel or F except in the Sb. form. e.g: D'ól mé,D'fhág mé but Sb. óladh fágadh
Do not confuse this regular verb with the irregular verb 'Feic' see.
The letter 'S' is not aspirated (ft) when it is followed by: C, F, M, P, T, V. E.G: Scuab sé;Stad sé;but Sheas sé.
In the M. ORD. Imperative we can use Éist and Éistigí listen for the 2nd. person sing,and plural of the verb 'Clois' or 'Cluin'.
In the 'Caite' 'I did', one may use Dhein mé and Níor dhein mé srl. instead of 'Rinne mé' and 'Ní dhearna mé srl.'
